{
  "name": "{{PREFIX}} {{SOURCE}} Baseline Refresh",
  "description": "Nightly rebuild of the UEBA behavioral baseline for {{SOURCE}}. Re-runs ueba_baseline_savelookup.pq against the trailing {{BASELINE_HOURS}}h so {{BASELINE_TABLE}} stays current, then the scheduled detection rule joins it. Bind the 'SentinelOne SDL' connection (Bearer) before activating, NOT the 'SentinelOne' mgmt connection (that signs as ApiToken and the /sdl/v2/api/queries action returns 500 'Header must start with Bearer'). Import with ?siteIds={{SITE_ID}}. For very large / high-cardinality sources where a single multi-day query exceeds the 60s action timeout, slice per day or run scripts/baseline_anomaly.py on a schedule instead.",
